20 Ford Fusion"> (24) 2020 Ford Fusion (24) Price Starting From $23,170 = 3 && !addedToCompare" > Compare = 3 && !addedToCompare" > Added To Compare Add To Compare Why We Picked It The Ford Fusion is a family-friendly vehicle with attractive offerings. Its back-row space lags the Accord slightly at 38.3 inches of legroom and 54.4 inches of hip room, but the back seat is flexible enough to anchor car seats in all three positions. The center seat can borrow LATCH anchors from either outboard seat or can use its own upper anchor. Trunk space is decent at 16 cubic-feet. The Fusion earned Good ratings in all crashworthiness categories from IIHS, but received a Poor rating for its headlights and no score for standard front vehicle-to-pedestrian crash prevention. The Fusion’s fuel economy numbers range from 23 to 42 mpg combined from a plug-in hybrid system. Ford ended production after the 2020 model year, though many dealers still have some in stock in 2021. The Fusion remains a competitive vehicle. The 2020 Ford Fusion earned Good ratings in all crashworthiness categories from IIHS, but received a Poor rating for its headlights and no score for standard front vehicle-to-pedestrian crash prevention. The Fusion’s fuel economy numbers range from 23 to 42 mpg combined from a plug-in hybrid system. Pros & Cons Available in a range of engine options Easy connectivity for mobile devices Stylish exterior No 2021 model (production ended 2020) Options quickly increase the price Interior isn’t quite as nice as some rivals Specs <best-of-specs :specs="specs" :show-mobile-ui="true"> Why We Picked It Pros & Cons Specs The Ford Fusion is a family-friendly vehicle with attractive offerings. Its back-row space lags the Accord slightly at 38.3 inches of legroom and 54.4 inches of hip room, but the back seat is flexible enough to anchor car seats in all three positions. The center seat can borrow LATCH anchors from either outboard seat or can use its own upper anchor. Trunk space is decent